# Compact UI Design Patterns

## General Principles

1. **Reduce padding**: Use `p-4` or `p-3` instead of `p-6` for compact components
2. **Smaller fonts**: Use `text-xs` or `text-sm` for secondary information, `text-[10px]` for labels
3. **Tighter spacing**: Use `gap-2` instead of `gap-4`, `mb-3` instead of `mb-6`
4. **Grid layouts**: Use responsive grids to maximize space efficiency
5. **Inline elements**: Place related information on the same line when possible

## Component Layout Patterns

### Compact Cards

```tsx
// Compact card with reduced padding
<div className="p-4 rounded-lg shadow">
  <div className="flex items-center justify-between mb-3">
    <h3 className="text-base font-bold">Title</h3>
    <span className="px-2 py-0.5 rounded text-xs">Badge</span>
  </div>
  {/* Content */}
</div>
```

### Grid Layouts for Forms

```tsx
// Two-column grid for related fields
<div className="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
  <div>
    <label className="block text-sm font-medium mb-2">Field 1</label>
    <input className="w-full px-4 py-2 rounded" />
  </div>
  <div>
    <label className="block text-sm font-medium mb-2">Field 2</label>
    <input className="w-full px-4 py-2 rounded" />
  </div>
</div>
```

### Compact Statistics Display

```tsx
// Compact stats with smaller fonts
<div className="grid grid-cols-3 gap-2">
  <div className="p-2.5 rounded">
    <div className="text-[10px] mb-0.5 font-medium">LABEL</div>
    <div className="text-lg font-bold leading-tight">Value</div>
    <div className="text-[10px] mt-0.5">Percentage</div>
  </div>
</div>
```

### Inline Status and Actions

```tsx
// Status badge and action button on same line
<div className="flex items-center justify-between mb-3">
  <div className="flex items-center gap-2">
    <h3 className="text-lg font-bold">Title</h3>
    <span className="text-xs px-2 py-0.5 rounded">Status</span>
  </div>
  <button className="px-2.5 py-1 rounded text-xs">Action</button>
</div>
```

## Voting Summary Component Pattern

See [VotingSummary.tsx](mdc:web/components/VotingSummary.tsx) for reference:

- **Collapsible sections**: Use toggle buttons to show/hide detailed information
- **Compact proposal cards**: Show essential info with minimal padding
- **Grid layouts**: Use `grid-cols-3` or `grid-cols-4` for statistics
- **Small progress bars**: Use `h-2.5` or `h-1.5` for compact progress indicators

## Proposal Card Pattern

See [ProposalCard.tsx](mdc:web/components/ProposalCard.tsx) for reference:

- **Remove redundant info**: Don't show proposal number if name is available
- **Inline status**: Place status badge next to title
- **Grid for details**: Use 2-column grid for proposal information
- **Compact vote display**: Smaller fonts and padding for vote statistics

## Button Placement

```tsx
// Place related information next to buttons
<div className="flex gap-2 items-center">
  <button>Action</button>
  {status && <div className="text-sm ml-2">Status: {status}</div>}
</div>
```

## Responsive Considerations

- **Mobile**: Stack elements vertically (`grid-cols-1`)
- **Desktop**: Use multi-column layouts (`md:grid-cols-2`, `md:grid-cols-4`)
- **Always test**: Ensure compact design remains readable on all screen sizes

